Micobial Analysis PART 2

  • Following analysis mainly used the phyloseq project following: https://yanhui09.github.io/microbiome_analysis/1_microbiome_r.html

  • All QWIIME output files can be found in folder /Raw Data/QIIME

# Merging data and building phyloseq project
otumat <- as.matrix(Table)  # This is the un-feature-table.tsv file
TAX = tax_table(as.matrix(Taxa))  # This is the taxonomy.tsv file
tree <-read.tree("tree.nwk") 
OTU= otu_table(otumat, taxa_are_rows = TRUE)
TAX= tax_table(TAX) #Taxa_clean_matched file
samples = sample_data(Metadata) #UVM-Metadata
ps <- phyloseq(OTU,TAX,samples,tree)
nsamples(ps)       # number of samples
[1] 176
ntaxa(ps)          # number of taxa (OTUs) #7975
[1] 7975
sample_variables(ps) # metadata variables
[1] "location"  "Room.Type" "Time"

Data Transformation

Total Sum method are used here

#Transformed the phyloseq object that is at species level before collapsing
ps.transformed= transform_sample_counts(ps, function(x) x / sum(x) )

Quality Control

Singleton, doubleton, mitochondria and chloroplast have already been removed in QIIME2 Here we remove 0.1% ASV

ps.transformed_f0.1<- prune_taxa(taxa_sums(ps.transformed)>0.001, ps.transformed) #
ntaxa(ps.transformed_f0.1)#number of taxa after removing 0.1% ASV
[1] 5092

Alpha Diversity: Shannon Index calculation

Alpha diversity is calculated with Shannon Index using using the vegan package

otu2 <- otu_table(ps.transformed_f0.1)
shannon <- diversity(otu2, index="shannon") 
write.csv(shannon,"shannon_index") # This file is used for statistical analysis

How does indoor daylight affects the indoor environmental microbiol composition at different time point?

PCoA Analysis

  • Principle coordinate analysis is used to visualized the dissimilarity between microbial diversity )beta-diversity
  • This dissimilarity distance are calculated based on 3 matrix: Weighted Unifrac and Unweighted Unifrac, and Bray-Curtis Distance
  • T0 refers to baseline, T1 means Day one of admission, and T3 refers to Day-3 of patient admission
  • View room in here indicates the EC window room

Baseline

Envir_T0_nb  <- subset_samples(Envir_T0_nb, sample_names(Envir_T0_nb) !='R4T0_AD') # This is an outlier
Envir_T0_nb.df=data.frame(sample_data(Envir_T0_nb))

Envir_T0_nb_wuf = phyloseq::distance(Envir_T0_nb, method="wunifrac")
ordination_Envir_T0_nb_wuf = ordinate(Envir_T0_nb, method="PCoA", distance=Envir_T0_nb_wuf)


plot_ordination(Envir_T0_nb, ordination_Envir_T0_nb_wuf, color="location",

Permanova

  • PERMANOVA test the statistical differences between the microbial composition with different variables, which also requires distance matrix measures. Test is perfomred using the vegan package
  • Weighted Unifrac is used for calculating distance matrix to see the effects of room type variables on microbial composition

Taxa Boxplot

  • Visualization of main taxa at different time point
  • Taxa included are relative abundance >1%
  • Legend (taxa) are sorted based on abundance from most abundant on the top left to least abundant on the right

ps3_nT0.melt <- psmelt(ps3_nb_T0_genus)
# change to character for easy-adjusted level
ps3_nT0.melt$Genus <- as.character(ps3_nT0.melt$Genus)

ps3_nT0.melt_v1 <- ps3_nT0.melt %>%
                  group_by(location, Genus) %>%
                  mutate(mean=mean(Abundance)) #Take the mean Abundance 

# select group mean > 1
keep1 <- unique(ps3_nT0.melt_v1$Genus[ps3_nT0.melt_v1$mean > 0.01])
ps3_nT0.melt_v1$Genus[!ps3_nT0.melt_v1$Genus %in% keep1] <- "< 1%"

#Rank and sort the legend based on the abundance
ps3_nT0.melt_v1_sum <- ps3_nT0.melt_v1 %>%
  group_by(Room.Type,location,Genus) %>%
  summarise(Abundance=sum(Abundance)) %>%
  mutate(Genus = factor(Genus, levels = unique(Genus))) %>%
  group_by(Room.Type, location) %>%
  arrange(Abundance, .by_group=TRUE) 

ps3_nT0.melt_v1_sum $location <- factor(ps3_nT0.melt_v1_sum$location, levels=c("Window","AirFilter", "AirDuct",
                                                                               "Outside-Blind", "Palm", "Saliva"))
#get color palette
ps3_colors = get_palette(palette = "npg",length(levels(ps3_nT0.melt_v1_sum$Genus)))
ggplot(ps3_nT0.melt_v1_sum, aes(x=location, y= Abundance)) + 
      geom_col(aes(fill=fct_reorder(Genus, Abundance)), color="black", lwd=0.2, position="fill") +
      labs(x=NULL, y="Relative Abundance %", fill="Genus",title = "Genus Composition in Regular and EC Window room at baseline") +
      scale_fill_manual(values=ps3_colors)+
      facet_grid(Room.Type~.) +
      guides(fill = guide_legend (reverse = TRUE, keywidth = 1, keyheight = 1))+
      theme(plot.title = element_text(size=14,hjust=0.5))
